Text.Value: In the carnage to come, you shall reach the peak of your holy magnificence.
The beady eye of tiny Sceleritas is upon you, do not forget that.
Have we always been together?
Poor Cruor, never stood a chance.
I was sent to guide you to your birthright, on the day my vile Lord reached his age of majority.
I was sent to guide you to your birthright, on the day my vile Lady reached her age of majority.
I was sent to guide you to your birthright, on the day my vile Liege reached their age of majority.
M-Master... You speak the truth. You became his Chosen, and will go on to even greater deeds.
I live to serve, as your Father made me. If I cannot serve...
I jest, cleaning is beneath my chief manservant.
That last run must have been the shortest time any Sceleritas lived! Can you beat the record?

EditorData.logicalname: DU KILLED BUTLER IN CAMP 3rd time

Text.Value: My Lord... you are the hero of a sad tale.
My Lady... you are the hero of a sad tale.
My dear genderless champion... you are the hero of a sad tale.
*Sceleritas seems unable to speak, ever since you commanded him not to.*
My destiny terrifies me still.
My fondest congratulations for your work in the Temple!
My favourite subject of conversation!
I shall attend to your miserable royal person with great care. You shall be well-groomed with my tincy talons. Yes, yes.
Yes, my Lord.
Yes, my Lady.
Yes, my Liege.
Will my Urges grow stronger, now Bhaal has such a hold over me?
Mmmmn. Oh. OH. That was euphoric. You're even better than you used to be.

EditorData.logicalname: DU KILLED BUTLER IN CAMP 1st time

Text.Value: My past.
Me? Serve Orin? I shall be sick! Fetch the Bucket of Bhaal!
Oh Master, I wish you could stand brutalising me forever.

EditorData.logicalname: DU KILLED BUTLER IN CAMP 4th time

Text.Value: Inquisite me. What do you wish to know of?
Cease your chattering! A Butler of mine will not speak unless spoken to!
How dare you? My life is my Master's alone to steal.
Not half as much as the world over will fear you.
Being in your service was an honour.
The only way for a Butler to die is if we are not of use to our Master. But you have always needed abundant assistance.
Well done! Well done indeed! On this eve, Sceleritas gazes upon perfection.
Why he chose to take one such as yourself as a retainer is beyond me.
Why she chose to take one such as yourself as a retainer is beyond me.
Why they chose to take one such as yourself as a retainer is beyond me.
It won't be long, Milord... It won't be long.
It won't be long, Milady... It won't be long.
It won't be long, Master... It won't be long.
Your presence will be tolerated in his company, if you do not interfere with his holy destiny.
Your presence will be tolerated in her company, if you do not interfere with her holy destiny.
Your presence will be tolerated in their company, if you do not interfere with their holy destiny.
Survive? I did not! it was my favourite death yet!
I have no further use for you, begone!
You turned into Bhaal! How did you survive?
You were merely reborn... with a silver spoon in your brain.
Perhaps you will be of use, still.
Orin was not special. She was but a grandchild of an aged Bhaalspawn. A mere weed of Bhaal's loins.
It appears that may be already underway. The drow is a fecund choice of mate. Well done!
Of course, Master! We will always need to sire more Bhaalspawn!
You.
I shall engrave that compliment on my heart.
Leave.
I hope we will stay together, always.
You make a Butler blush!
What exactly are you?
Bhaal gave out all of his seed long ago, in the time of Sarevok.
Orin had her own Butler, who she insolently killed on his first visit, claiming she didn't need him to follow Bhaal.
Oh no! There are far more important matters at hand. But if you must waste time thinking of your Butler, I will attend to your curiosity.
Can I ever get my memories back?
No Bhaalspawn has ever borne the Urge, the holy guarantee of murder. It was woven into your blood alone.
A friend? You considered me 'a friend'?
I have some questions.
Wait, Master, if you ask me to- Mmmpfh!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Halfway through the sentence the butler's mouth snaps shut.

Text.Value: You didn't kick him or spit on him or anything! I was so shocked I almost fainted!
Master, you spoil me so. You have murdered me so sweetly time and time again.
Begone! I don't need you any more!
Hopefully the near-slaughter of your partner taught them the wisdom of obeying your every command.
This is getting rather silly, my Liege. But I am enjoying myself.

EditorData.logicalname: DU KILLED BUTLER IN CAMP 7+ times

Text.Value: Oh, thank you, thank you! You shall not regret this, godly villain!
Hee hee! Sceleritas is back again!

EditorData.logicalname: DU KILLED BUTLER IN CAMP 2nd time

Text.Value: Your command is my wish. Your demand is my desire.
You shall be a graven God, my demiurge. All you must do now is heed your Father's advice when the time comes.
Hello, you must be one of Master's other servants.
Why are you at rest? Start cleaning the camp!
Mmmrph hrrmm!

EditorData.NodeContext: Making noises through a closed mouth - cannot talk

Text.Value: But I worry you are distracted from your glory. There are others to kill besides me!
You do not have a charm placed upon you to clear your memory-stores, nor an enchantment befuddling you.
Hee! Hee! Splendid jest, Master.
Although if they are not up to the task we may need to find you a breeding-mate. Or ten.
You may speak again.
There was one time you gave a beggar some coin while we were en route to the Devil's Fee.
MMMMMMNN!
MMMMMMRRRRM.

EditorData.logicalname: NON DU PLAYER KILLED SILENCED BUTLER

Text.Value: As long as there have been Bhaalspawn, there have been Butlers, but Bhaal only makes them for the children he has use of.
Can you tell me the worst thing I ever did?
I am but a table-scrap of Bhaal's will. He will send me to aid and protect you, until you have need of me no more.
If this is how it must be... Goodbye, Master.
Oh, my pustulating godhead! Why do you degrade yourself, wearing the shameful hatpiece of a mere servant?
How did you end up serving me, and not Orin?
You were not conceived. Bhaal sculpted you from a drop of his own gore.
At once. I will shatter some glasses and sprinkle the fragments in the beds of your other followers. Keep their dreams bloody.
Orin was born and raised in the Temple, but you spent many years on your own before you found your way back home.
Now, as you are the last true recipient of your Father's blessing, I suspect I am the last living Butler.
But if you don't need me, I shall perish. Once and for all.
Wash the dishes!
Who was my mother, if Bhaal was my Father?
Pathetic creature!
Aaah! Master! I'm sorry, I'm ever-so sorry to forget my other duties! What a wretch I am! I'm not even worthy of being your scullery maid.

EditorData.NodeContext: Startled, realises he has done poorly

Text.Value: Orin dug, Orin scooped, Orin dissected. Your brain is damaged forever.
Know that I love him best.
Know that I love her best.
Know that I love them best.
Your tedious sister believed she was ending you when she drilled the wee tadpole-cavern in your head.
You and the Urge are wedded, now. One body, one mind.
Hence you have such diverse talents. But you were awful from the very first day you set foot amongst the ichored altars.
Away! Attend to your duties! Lazy little maid you are!

Another matter...

Don't make me go, Master! Please!
It is an honour to see you look so fetching, but let me dress you properly on the morrow.
As he does each time I expire by your side, Bhaal has sent you another loyal Sceleritas, to watch over and adore you.
I love you when you hurt me, Master.
